Alvarion Buys Clariton for About $4 Million, Calcalist Says

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-05-03T06:05:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/alvarion-buys-clariton-for-about-4-million-calcalist-says.html
Alvarion Ltd. (ALVR)  purchased Clariton
Networks Ltd., an Israeli company which develops products
enabling delivery of cellular voice and data traffic to homes,
for about $4 million, Calcalist said, without disclosing where
it obtained the information.  A message left on the cell phone of a spokesman for
Alvarion was not immediately answered.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Calev Ben-David at 
 cbendavid@bloomberg.net  